How can this be corrected? </description><pubDate>Thu, 18 Jun 2015 17:27:08 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/6140/wrong-battery-percentage-shown-in-status-bar/</guid></item><item><title>Answer by oberon for &lt;p&gt;I've just setup i3 on my notebook and when the battery is full it states it's at 86,42%.
How can this be corrected? &lt;/p&gt;
 </title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/6140/wrong-battery-percentage-shown-in-status-bar/?answer=6141#post-id-6141</link><description>To have the value refer to the last full capacity instead of the design capacity of the battery, add in your .i3status.conf:

    last_full_capacity = true
for more details have a look here: http://i3wm.org/i3status/manpage.html#_battery ;)</description><pubDate>Thu, 18 Jun 2015 17:33:55 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/6140/wrong-battery-percentage-shown-in-status-bar/?answer=6141#post-id-6141</guid></item></channel></rss>